Hi hi, if I want to make a pandan flavoured egg tart . What adjustments can I do ? Thanks so much!!

Girl’s 1st attempt to make egg tarts! IMO tastes even better than TC bakery! She did everything from scratch all by herself while mommy helps with the cleaning & washing.😄 .

My family loves eating Hong Kong Style egg tarts and so far we have been buying it from our favourite bakery. Now with this recipe we can bake it at home! 😍 .
.

Swipe to the 4th pic for the cross section - look how smooth the egg custard is and how thin and even the crust!.
.

Here’s sharing the egg tart recipe which my girl has adapted from Tasty for the fillings and she can’t remember where for the dough. Please watch the short video at the end for reference..
.
. . 【𝐇𝐨𝐧𝐠 𝐊𝐨𝐧𝐠 𝐒𝐭𝐲𝐥𝐞 𝐄𝐠𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐬 - 𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐛𝐲 𝐁𝐚𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐢 】.
.
𝘿𝙤𝙪𝙜𝙝 𝙄𝙣𝙜𝙧𝙚𝙙𝙞𝙚𝙣𝙩𝙨:
200g Blue Jacket Unbleached cake flour
115g Lurpak unsalted butter *
40g SIS icing sugar 
2 tablespoon beaten egg (taken from eggs for filling) 
1/8 tsp sea salt .
*Important to use premium & good quality butter for a better taste, flavor and aroma.
.

𝘾𝙪𝙨𝙩𝙖𝙧𝙙 𝙁𝙞𝙡𝙡𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙄𝙣𝙜𝙧𝙚𝙙𝙞𝙚𝙣𝙩𝙨: 
4 eggs beaten (save 2 tbsp for dough)
180ml hot water
6 tbsp caster sugar
1/8 tsp sea salt
60ml evaporated milk 
1 tsp pure vanilla bean paste (we use Nielsen-Massey brand) .

𝙈𝙚𝙩𝙝𝙤𝙙𝙨: (𝙬𝙖𝙩𝙘𝙝 𝙢𝙮 𝙫𝙞𝙙𝙚𝙤 𝙖𝙗𝙤𝙫𝙚 𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙧𝙚𝙛𝙚𝙧𝙚𝙣𝙘𝙚) 
1. For the pastry: Sift flour, sugar & salt. Add in softened butter and bring mixture together using hands. (DO NOT over knead or pastry will be tough).
.
2. Add in beaten egg to form a dough. Cling wrap then refrigerate for 30 mins till firm. .
3. For the custard filling: Melt sugar & salt in hot water. Let cool. .
4. Add in eggs, sugar water, evaporated milk & vanilla paste. Stir & combine well. .
5. Strain the mixture to ensure no lumps. Chill in fridge. .
6. Preheat the oven top and bottom heat 200°C.
.
7. Divide dough into 13 portions. Take a portion, roll round, flatten, place in tart shell and press around with fingers. .
8. Pour custard filling into the shells until about 80% full. .
9. Bake for 15-20 mins until a toothpick insert can stand in the egg tart. .
